=== Festival ===
The following festivals are held at Tarumi Shrine each year.
* Monthly Festival/Monthly Festival (1st and 15th of every month)
* Fudosha Goma (8th of every month)
* Saitan Festival (January 1st)
* Tarumi Ebisu (January 10th)
* Donto Festival (January 15th)
*Setsubun Festival (February 3rd)
* Yoimiya (Otabisho Festival) (May 20th)
* Spring Festival (May 21st)
* Summer Purification (June 30th)
* Yoimiya (Otabisho Festival) (October 20th)
* Autumn Festival (October 21st) - ``Regular Festival''.
* Great Purification (December 31st)

=== Appeared works ===
* 1 poem from volume 8 of "{{ill|lt=Man'yoshu|Q834321|WD=Q834321|1=Man'yōshū}}" (Man'yoshu has three poems in which Tarumi is read, but there are some theories that it is a proper noun and some that it is a common noun) <ref name="Historic Book"/>{{Sfn|Tarumi Shrine (Shikinaisha)|1977}}{{Sfn|Tarumi Shrine (Gods)|2000}}<ref>New Edition of Japanese Classical Literature Complete Works 7 Man'yoshu (2), Shogakukan, 2004 (Japan Knowledge Edition), p. 293. </ref><ref>Ichinosuke Takagi et al.'s notes, "Japanese Classical Literature System, Manyoshu 2", Iwanami Shoten, 1959, P.283</ref>
{{Cquote|{{Small|Spring poem<br />Prince Shiki's poem}}<br />　Atop the stone-running ``Tarumi'''', you might be able to enjoy the budding spring of the rustle |20px||{{ill|lt=Prince Shiki|Q11072254|WD=Q11072254|1=Prince Shiki}}, "{{ill|lt=Man'yoshu|Q834321|WD=Q834321|1=Man'yōshū}}" Volume 8 No. 1418<ref>[http://infux03.inf.edu.yamaguchi-u.ac.jp/~manyou/ver2_2/manyou_kekka2.php?kekka=08/1418 08/1418] (Yamaguchi University "Manyoushu Search System"). </ref>{{Sfn|Shinto/Shrine Historical Materials Collection}}}}

